(AP) -- Obesity is not as dangerous for elderly people as it is for the middle-aged or young adults. ``The absolute risk of dying gets higher and higher as you get older until you die, but the importance of obesity as a risk factor decreases,'' said Ralf Bender. ``Obesity is a major public health problem at any age, and this study does nothing to suggest that that has changed,'' said Dr. JoAnn Manson, an endocrinologist at Harvard Medical School. In the latest study, researchers studied 6,193 obese men and women who ranged in age from 18 to 74, following them
